The discard syntax is simply a syntactic sugar to suppress the warning of &quot;the return value of this expression is unused&quot;. These two lines compile to the same IL:

    _ = Example();
    Example();

They both become the same `call` instruction. 

Therefore, if `Example()` works for you, so will `_ = Example()`.

